Summary:
This is the netlist form of the RC high-pass filter. The capacitor sits in series with the input so that DC and very low frequencies are blocked from the output node.
The resistor to ground defines the output load and gives the capacitor a discharge path.

Line-by-line:
`Vin N001 0 SINE(1 1 25000) AC 1` is the source.
`C1 N001 Output_high_pass 100µ` is the coupling capacitor.
`R1 Output_high_pass 0 1` is the load resistor.
`.ac dec 1000 10 100k` performs frequency analysis.
The comments explain that the capacitor removes DC and establish the cutoff equation.

Netlist meaning:
At low frequency the capacitor looks open, so output drops.
At high frequency the capacitor looks more like a short, so the output approaches the input.
